image.altText: A crowd gathers outside a gate while several people try to break through the gate

props.synopsis: Sixteen people have died in violent riots in Papua New Guinea after some residents took advantage of police being on strike to set shops and businesses alight in the capital.

title.children: Violent riots in PNG leave 16 people dead, as MP calls for PM Marape to step down

image.altText: Water flows over the spillway of Paradise Dam near Bundaberg in southern Queensland in March 2013.

title.children: Paradise Dam operators warn 60,000 people living downstream that its 'safety standards' fall short

image.altText: A person in a harness climbs towards the top of a damaged gumtree.

props.synopsis: As tens of thousands of insurance claims are lodged in the wake of the deadly Christmas storms, there's a big damage bill many property owners will have to stump up for themselves.

title.children: Clearing trees and deadly 'hangers': The Christmas storm damage bill that's not covered by insurance

image.altText: Woman's hand holds a credit card in front of a computer

props.synopsis: Online retailer The Iconic has failed to provide basic security measures to verify its customers' payment details when placing an order, putting its 2.1 million customers at risk of being defrauded, cybersecurity experts say

title.children: A basic security failure from The Iconic has put millions of its customers at risk of being defrauded

image.altText: A red and white logo sticking out of a building which reads Post Office Bureau de Change.

image.altText: Composite of a man and a bullet hole in a glass door.

image.altText: three adults, a child and two dogs pose for a santa photo

image.altText: A doctor holds a stethoscope in two clasped hands

image.altText: Alex de Minaur clenches his fist during a US Open match against Daniil Medvedev.

title.children: Aussie star Alex de Minaur cops brutal opening round match ahead of Sunday's Australian Open

image.altText: Dark storm clouds swallow blue sunlit skies

image.altText: Jigalong Remote Community School

image.altText: Girls get into Australia Day mood in Melbourne.

image.altText: A composite image of an Israeli tank next to a set of blue scales.

props.synopsis: International law experts say South Africa's genocide case against Israel could put political pressure on Israel and its allies, forcing a change of tactics in the Gaza war.

image.altText: A large intercontinental ballistic missile is lauched vertically  from a truck, with flames from its exhaust hitting the ground.

image.altText: A woman with a neutral expression looking at the camera.

image.altText: Man in screengrab behind bars

image.altText: three men in black shirts looking at the camera

image.altText: A woman and a young man.

image.altText: Tamiko Gleeson and her husband Daniel stand in an empty room under construction. They hold their dog and smile at the camera

props.synopsis: There's nothing like a renovation to throw your life into disarray, but it can be a new level of chaos while also living in your home. These are the nuggets of wisdom for how to survive, from those who've done it .

title.children: The story of 'Giganto', the world's largest ape, and why it disappeared forever
